### General Bits and bobs ###
$ sudo yum update
$ sudo yum install epel-release krb5-workstation krb5-libs krb5-auth-dialog gcc gcc-c++ java-1.8.0-openjdk python-devel python-pip
$ sudo yum group install 'Development Tools'

### Elastic Stack ###
- Follow https://computingforgeeks.com/how-to-install-elk-stack-on-centos-7-fedora-29/
- Start the services without the .service on the end

