### ROOT ###
$ wget https://root.cern.ch/download/root_v5.34.36.Linux-centos7-x86_64-gcc4.8.tar.gz
$ tar xzvf root_v5.34.36.Linux-centos7-x86_64-gcc4.8.tar.gz
$ . root/bin/thisroot.sh

### BOOST ###
$ wget https://dl.bintray.com/boostorg/release/1.68.0/source/boost_1_68_0.tar.gz
$ tar -xzf boost_1_*
$ cd boost_1_*
$ sudo ./bootstrap.sh --prefix=/opt/boost
$ sudo ./b2 install --prefix=/opt/boost --with=all
- Add boost lib and include paths to MAKEFILE

### MetricBeat ###
$ curl -L -O https://artifacts.elastic.co/downloads/beats/metricbeat/metricbeat-6.7.1-x86_64.rpm
$ sudo rpm -vi metricbeat-6.7.1-x86_64.rpm
- edit /etc/metricbeat/metricbeat.yml to configure elasticsearch and kibana
$ sudo metricbeat modules enable system
$ sudo metricbeat setup
$ sudo service metricbeat start

### Alerting (ElastAlert) ###
$ sudo pip install "setuptools>=11.3"
$ sudo pip install elastalert

### elasticclient ###
$ sudo yum install perl-core libtemplate-perl zlib-devel openssl-devel libssh2-devel libmicrohttpd-devel curl-devel gtest-devel
- Then just follow instructions on https://github.com/seznam/elasticlient

